Class SQLDatabaseEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.bot.spring.SQLDatabaseEngine

  • public class SQLDatabaseEngine
extends java.lang.Object
    The SQLDatabaseEngine is the PostgreSQL database engine that handles all functions that accesses the database.

      • writeUserInfo

        public void writeUserInfo(java.lang.String userId,
                          int age,
                          java.lang.String gender,
                          double height,
                          double weight,
                          java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> allergies,
                          java.lang.String diet,
                          java.lang.String topic,
                          java.lang.String state)
        Writes the input user info into the database. Writes into both the userinfo and userallergies databases.
        Parameters:
        userId - the user's Line ID.
        age - the user's age.
        gender - the user's gender, either "male" or "female".
        height - the user's height, in meters.
        weight - the user's weight, in kilograms.
        allergies - a list of the user's allergies.
        diet - the user's dieting goals, either "little_diet", "normal" or "serious_diet".
        topic - the user's topic within Rivescript.
        state - the user's state within Rivescript.
